            <h1>
                                Researcher Training Guidelines for OPRS Live            </h1>
          
          
                <h2 class="element-invisible">You are here</h2><div class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> <span class="separator">></span> <a href="/compliance">Compliance</a> <span class="separator">></span> <a href="/compliance/irb" title="">Human Subjects & IRB</a> <span class="separator">></span> <a href="/irb/investigators-research-staff/preparation-submission">For Investigators & Research Staff</a> <span class="separator">></span> <a href="/irb/getting-started">Submission</a> <span class="separator">></span> <a href="/compliance/human-subjects-irb/investigators-research-staff/submission/oprslive-beta">OPRS Live (beta)</a> <span class="separator">></span> <a href="/compliance/human-subjects-irb/investigators-research-staff/submission/oprs-live-beta/researcher" class="active">Researcher Training Guidelines for OPRS Live</a></div>          
        
        
        
            
      </div>

      <div class="layout-content main-content">
      
<section class="block block-system">
  
  
  <div class="content">
    <div>
      <article class="page node full">

  
  
  <div class="content">
    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even"><p><strong><a href="/sites/default/files/OPRSLive_Guidelines.pdf">Printable Version</a></strong></p>
<div class="accordions">
<p><article class="accordion collapsed"><header class="accordion-header"><br /><div class="icon"></div>
<div class="desc">
<h1>Basic Information</h1>
</div>
<p></p></header><br /><div class="accordion-body">
<ol><li>OPRS Live production link: <a href="https://oprslive.ovcr.uic.edu">https://oprslive.ovcr.uic.edu</a></li>
<li>If you are a new user, you will need to register by clicking on ‘Create Account’ and entering your name and UIC email address.* You will then receive a temporary password via email which you can use to log in. After your initial log in, you can change your password by clicking ‘Change Password’ under your name in the upper right corner of the screen.</li>
<li>If you are already registered and have forgotten your password, click on ‘Forgot Password’ on the main log in screen and follow the instructions. You will be sent a new temporary password via email</li>
</ol><p>*If you are new to UIC or have not completed investigator training, you will need to follow the instructions under ‘Create Account’ to be added to the OPRS research personnel database prior to registering.</p></div>
<p></p></article></p>
<p><article class="accordion collapsed"><header class="accordion-header"><br /><div class="icon"></div>
<div class="desc">
<h1>Creating a New Initial Application</h1>
</div>
<p></p></header><br /><div class="accordion-body">
<ol><li>Click ‘Start New Submission’ on the Researcher dashboard.</li>
<li>Select the Submission Type (Initial Review) and indicate the College and Department of the Principal Investigator (PI). Answer the screening questions as applicable and click ‘OK’.<br />
	[Note: Based on the answers to the screening questions, applications will be directed to either the Full Submission or Quick Submission process. Most applications will be created as Full Submissions, meaning that the submission will be routed for electronic signatures. Applications submitted for a Determination of Whether an Activity Represents Human Subjects Research, applications for a Humanitarian Use Device, and applications submitted for External Review will be directed to the Quick Submission process. Quick Submissions require signed documents* to be uploaded to the system, as they are not routed for electronic signatures. (*Determination applications do not require signatures.)]</li>
<li>Enter your protocol title and other requested information, then click ‘Create’.</li>
<li>Verify and Save submission details. If your application is a Quick Submission, you can upload your submission documents and click ‘Submit’. For Full Submissions, continue with steps 5-9.</li>
<li>Click ‘Next’ to be taken to the ‘Smart Forms’ tab. Click on ‘Initial Review Questionnaire’ and respond to all items. If the PI will be a student, resident, or fellow, be sure to answer “Yes” to question 10. Click ‘Save’.</li>
<li>Click ‘Next’ to be taken to the ‘Attachments’ tab. The responses to the Smart Form questionnaire will determine what attachments may be required for your submission, and you will see attachment placeholders for those documents. OPRS forms appearing in blue can be downloaded directly from OPRS Live, completed, saved, and then uploaded for submission. Forms/documents not available for download can be uploaded directly from your computer. Multiple documents can be uploaded under any placeholder. Attachments for which no specific placeholder is created can be uploaded under ‘Other Documents’; if you have no such attachments, please be sure to check the box “I have no document to upload” to change the status of ‘Other Documents’ to ‘Completed’ in the ‘Attachments’ table.<br />
	(See guidance on ‘Formatting File Names for OPRS Live Attachments’ and all OPRS forms and templates available for download at <a href="http://research.uic.edu/compliance/human-subjects-irb/forms">http://research.uic.edu/compliance/human-subjects-irb/forms</a>.)</li>
<li>Once the status for each attachment is noted as ‘Completed’ click on ‘Next’ to go to the ‘Routing’ tab. Enter PI and Faculty Sponsor information, as applicable.</li>
<li>Verify the Department and Department Head information. The application will be routed to the individual listed as Department Head for approval.
<p>	If the Department Head is part of the research, then be sure to select/assign the Department Head Supervisor before submitting the application. Doing so will route the submission to the Department Head Supervisor for approval, as required by OPRS policy when the Department Head is a member of the research team. If the Department Head Supervisor is also part of the research, then that individual’s supervisor should be selected to approve the submission.</p></li>
<li>Click ‘Next’ to go to the ‘Submit’ tab. Check the box to accept the Assurance statement/Terms and Conditions, then click ‘Submit’.
<p>	Note that while any member of the research team (e.g., Research Coordinator or Co-Investigator) can create a new Initial Review submission, only the PI or Faculty Sponsor may submit an application. If someone other than the PI or Faculty Sponsor has created the submission, the “Notify PI” button will be visible and should be used to inform the PI that an application is pending the final submission.</p>
<p>	The PI will receive email updates as the submission is routed for Faculty Sponsor (if applicable) and Department Head approval, and when the submission is accepted by the OPRS Front Desk.</p></li>
</ol></div>
<p></p></article></p>
<p><article class="accordion collapsed"><header class="accordion-header"><br /><div class="icon"></div>
<div class="desc">
<h1>Creating a non-Initial Review submission (i.e., Continuing Review, Amendment, Final Report, Unanticipated Problem Report</h1>
</div>
<p></p></header><br /><div class="accordion-body">
<ol><li>Click on ‘Start New Submission’ on the Researcher dashboard.</li>
<li>Select the Submission Type (i.e., Continuing Review, Amendment, etc.) and enter the Protocol Number. Click ‘OK’.</li>
<li>Verify the Submission Type, and select the applicable Review Process. Save and Close.</li>
<li>Verify and Save the Submission Details.</li>
<li>Follow steps 5-9 as noted above for the New Initial Application to complete the Smart Form, Attachments, Routing, and Submit tabs. </li></ol></div>
<p></p></article></p><p><article class="accordion collapsed"><header class="accordion-header"><br /><div class="icon"></div>
<div class="desc">
<h1>Creating a Response to Modifications or Deferral</h1>
</div>
<p></p></header><br /><div class="accordion-body">
<ol><li>Click on ‘My Active Protocols’ in the Researcher dashboard.
<ol><li>You will see a table of your active protocols. Protocols with submissions requiring an action will have a blue ‘Action’ button under the ‘Action Required’ column.</li>
<li>Click ‘Action’ for the desired protocol and scroll down to see a table of all submissions made for that particular protocol. Individual submissions requiring a response will have a ‘Take Action’ button in the ‘Submit Mods’ column.</li>
<li>Click ‘Take Action’ and verify the information. Click ‘OK’.</li>
</ol></li>
<li>Verify and Save the Submission Details. If changes are required to the Smart Form questionnaire, click on the Form Name and click ‘Start Modifications’ to unlock the form. Make any changes, then Save.</li>
<li>To upload Attachments, select ‘View/Upload’ for the applicable form type and click ‘Start Modifications’. This will unlock the Attachment and change the status to ‘Incomplete’ in the Attachments table. Click on ‘View/Upload’ again to upload new/revised documents. Please be sure to attach both a tracked changes and an unmarked (all changes accepted) version of each revised document.</li>
<li>Once all revisions have been made, proceed with the Routing and Submit tabs. </li></ol></div>
<p></p></article></p><p><article class="accordion collapsed"><header class="accordion-header"><br /><div class="icon"></div>
<div class="desc">
<h1>Faculty Sponsor – Approval of Student Submissions</h1>
</div>
<p></p></header><br /><div class="accordion-body">
<ol><li>Click on ‘Student Submissions Ready to Approve’ in the Faculty Sponsor dashboard. You will see a list of the student submissions pending your approval.</li>
<li>Click on the blue Submission ID. You will see the PI and submission details. Here you can download and view the submission documents.</li>
<li>You can Accept or Reject the submission and enter any comments, then Save. If you Accept the submission, it will be routed to the Department Head for approval. If you Reject the submission, it will revert back to the student PI where any required changes can be made before re-submission. </li></ol></div>
<p></p></article></p><p><article class="accordion collapsed"><header class="accordion-header"><br /><div class="icon"></div>
<div class="desc">
<h1>How to Get Help</h1>
</div>
<p></p></header><br /><div class="accordion-body">
<p>Help Content and Contact Information can be found under the Help tab after logging in. Help Content includes videos and text instructions for various common questions about using the OPRS Live system.</p>
<p>If further assistance is needed, the following Contact Information is also included under the Help tab:</p>
<ol><li>For questions about technical issues: Email <strong><a href="mailto:oprslivesupport@uic.edu">oprslivesupport@uic.edu</a>.</strong></li>
<li>For questions about the IRB process, policies, and submission requirements: Email <a href="mailto:oprslive-irbprocess@uic.edu"><strong>oprslive-irbprocess@uic.edu</strong></a> OR call OPRS at 312-996-1711</li>
<li>For updates to name, department, contact information and training: Email <a href="mailto:rwdataentry@uic.edu"><strong>rwdataentry@uic.edu</strong></a> OR call OPRS at 312-996-1711</li>
<li>For questions about specific protocols, including review status: Please directly contact the staff of the IRB to which your protocol was assigned. If you are unsure of this information, contact the OPRS front desk at 312-996-1711 and have your protocol number ready.</li>
</ol></div>
<p></p></article></p></div>
</div></div></div>  </div>

  
</article>
    </div>
  </div>
  
